# DDD Infrastructure / Persistence Layer

**Rule: implements domain interfaces using Prisma. Never leaks Prisma types into the domain or application layers.**

## Infrastructure Folder Structure

```
infrastructure/
│
├── persistence/                        ← Database — Prisma repository implementations
│   ├── order.repository.ts             ← extends PrismaCrudRepositoryBase, implements IOrderRepository
│   ├── order-item.repository.ts        ← child entity repo (only if independently persisted)
│
├── external/                           ← Outbound HTTP — REST / GraphQL / SOAP clients
│   ├── exchange-rate/
│   │   ├── exchange-rate.client.ts     ← implements IExchangeRatePort
│   │   ├── exchange-rate.client.spec.ts
│   │   └── index.ts
│   └── inventory/
│       ├── inventory.client.ts         ← implements IInventoryPort
│       └── index.ts
│
├── messaging/                          ← Message broker — Kafka / RabbitMQ / SQS
│   ├── producers/
│   │   └── order-events.producer.ts    ← implements IOrderEventPublisher port
│   └── consumers/
│       └── order-events.consumer.ts    ← subscribes to topic, delegates to use case
│
├── cache/                              ← Caching wrappers (Redis, in-memory)
│   ├── cached-order.repository.ts      ← wraps OrderPrismaRepository with cache
│   └── cached-exchange-rate.client.ts  ← wraps ExchangeRateHttpClient with cache
│
└── adapters/                           ← Other port implementations (storage, email, SMS, etc.)
    ├── google-drive-storage.adapter.ts ← implements IStoragePort
    └── sendgrid-email.adapter.ts       ← implements IEmailPort
```

**Key principle:** Every file in `infrastructure/` implements a domain or application interface. Nothing in this folder is ever imported by `domain/` or `application/` directly — they always consume through their interface token.

---

## Concrete Repository (`infrastructure/persistence/*.repository.ts`)

Every Prisma repository:
- Extends `PrismaCrudRepositoryBase<PrismaClient, 'delegateKey', DomainEntity, Id, Filter>`
- Implements the domain-layer interface `IXxxRepository`
- Is decorated with `@Injectable()`

### Five required mapping hooks

These are the only methods that touch Prisma types. Everything else stays in the domain.

| Hook | Direction | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `toDomain(row)` | Prisma row → Domain entity | Reconstruct the aggregate from a DB row |
| `toCreateInput(entity)` | Domain entity → Prisma `create.data` | Map domain fields to DB columns for insert |
| `toUpdateInput(id, entity)` | Domain entity → Prisma `update.data` | Map domain fields to DB columns for update (exclude `id`) |
| `toUniqueWhere(id)` | id → `where: { id }` | Build the unique lookup clause |
| `toFilterWhere(filter?)` | Filter DTO → Prisma `where` | Build list/count filter clause |

### Two behavioural flags

| Flag | Default | When to override |
|---|---|---|
| `defaultOrderBy()` | `undefined` | Return e.g. `{ createdAt: 'desc' }` for consistent list ordering |
| `supportsSoftDelete()` | `false` | Return `true` if the table has a `deletedAt` column |

```ts
// ✅ Canonical example — ApiKeyRepository
@Injectable()
export class ApiKeyRepository
  extends PrismaCrudRepositoryBase<PrismaClient, 'authApiKey', ApiKey, string, ApiKeyFilter>
  implements IApiKeyRepository {

  constructor(database: BasePrismaService, eventEmitter: EventEmitter2) {
    super(database as any, 'authApiKey', eventEmitter);
  }

  // Prisma row → Domain model
  protected toDomain(row: { id: string; apiKey: string; ... }): ApiKey {
    return new ApiKey({
      id: row.id,
      key: row.apiKey,          // DB column name differs from domain field name
      expiresAt: row.expiresAt ?? undefined,
    });
  }

  // Domain model → Prisma create payload
  protected toCreateInput(entity: ApiKey) {
    return {
      id: entity.id,
      apiKey: entity.key,       // domain field name differs from DB column name
      permissions: entity.permissions,
      expiresAt: entity.expiresAt,
    };
  }

  // Domain model → Prisma update payload (never include id in data)
  protected toUpdateInput(_id: string, entity: ApiKey) {
    return {
      permissions: entity.permissions,
      expiresAt: entity.expiresAt,
      lastUsedAt: entity.lastUsedAt,
      updatedAt: entity.updatedAt,
    };
  }

  protected toUniqueWhere(id: string) { return { id }; }

  protected toFilterWhere(filter?: ApiKeyFilter) {
    return {
      ...(filter?.name && { name: { contains: filter.name, mode: 'insensitive' } }),
      ...(filter?.permissions && { permissions: { hasSome: filter.permissions } }),
    };
  }

  protected defaultOrderBy() { return { createdAt: 'desc' }; }
  protected supportsSoftDelete() { return false; }

  // Custom query beyond standard CRUD — use this.delegate directly
  async findByKeyId(key: string): Promise<ApiKey | null> {
    const row = await this.delegate.findUnique({ where: { apiKeyId: key } });
    return row ? this.toDomain(row) : null;
  }
}
```

